race.comment: PROSPECTOR'S PICK (9) is first-up today on the back of a strong trial at Belmont recently. He's a two-time winner fresh and he's well placed from the draw with a number of his rivals drawn wide. Rates highly on his form last campaign and can return a winner with CJP in the saddle. BLACK ORA (4) gets the blinkers on for the first time today following a narrow defeat as an odds-on fave last time out. The wide draw doesn't hurt as she was getting back and winning to begin this campaign. Can continue to raise the bar for Pike and looks the main danger. ROLLING RULER (14) is an exciting gelding on the rise, winning strongly last time out in easier company. His ratings suggest he's right up to this grade, though he will need some luck from an outside barrier. Can make his presence felt. AHYEAHRIGHTO (6) goes well fresh and has claims from an inside draw. JAZ SESSION (11) is third-up now and can feature with a bit of luck from the gate.
